FORMAT: 1A
HOST: http://localhost:8000

# Library Management API

Demo API quản lý thư viện bằng API Blueprint.

# Group Books

## Books Collection [/books]

### List all books [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
          {
            "id": "B001",
            "title": "Clean Architecture",
            "author": "Robert C. Martin",
            "year": 2017,
            "availableCopies": 5
          }
        ]

### Create a new book [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "title": "Domain-Driven Design",
          "author": "Eric Evans",
          "year": 2003,
          "availableCopies": 3
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
          "id": "B002",
          "title": "Domain-Driven Design",
          "author": "Eric Evans",
          "year": 2003,
          "availableCopies": 3
        }

## Book Detail [/books/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: B001 (string) - Book ID

### Retrieve a book [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "id": "B001",
          "title": "Clean Architecture",
          "author": "Robert C. Martin",
          "year": 2017,
          "availableCopies": 5
        }

+ Response 404

# Group Members

## Members Collection [/members]

### List all members [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
          {
            "id": "M001",
            "name": "Nguyen Van A",
            "email": "a@example.com"
          }
        ]

### Create a member [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "name": "Tran Thi B",
          "email": "b@example.com"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
          "id": "M002",
          "name": "Tran Thi B",
          "email": "b@example.com"
        }

# Group Loans

## Loans Collection [/loans]

### Borrow a book [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "bookId": "B001",
          "memberId": "M001"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
          "id": "L001",
          "bookId": "B001",
          "memberId": "M001",
          "status": "BORROWED",
          "borrowedAt": "2026-03-20T09:30:00Z"
        }

## Return Loan [/loans/{id}/return]

+ Parameters
    + id: L001 (string) - Loan ID

### Return a borrowed book [POST]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "id": "L001",
          "bookId": "B001",
          "memberId": "M001",
          "status": "RETURNED",
          "borrowedAt": "2026-03-20T09:30:00Z",
          "returnedAt": "2026-03-25T09:30:00Z"
        }
